# ----------- INSTRUCTIONS -------------------------------------- >8 -|
#             See https://www.conventionalcommits.org for details.
#             Choose <type> from options below.
#             Add an <id> or <context> for reference where relevant.
#             Supply a <message> in <verb> <detail> message.
#             When in doubt, use 'wip'.
# ----------- MAJOR --------------------------------------------------|
# feat!     : BREAKING CHANGES (change, refactor, retire)
# feat      : major new feature (new)
# ----------- MINOR --------------------------------------------------|
# feat      : minor new feature (add, enchance, deprecate)
# refactor  : change artefacts (move, rename, combine, separate)
# defect    : correct a defect (stub, correct, revert)
# ----------- PATCH --------------------------------------------------|
# dep       : modify dependencies (add, update, remove)
# doc       : documentation (add, update, refactor, remove)
# perf      : performace enhancement (optimize, increase)
# sec       : security (<verb> dependency, code, system)
# style     : idiomatic and stylistic changes (format, implement)
# ----------- NONE ---------------------------------------------------|
# chore     : unclassified commit
# cicd      : pipeline updates
# build     : build system updates
# merge     : merge branches
# test      : test functionality (add, update, remove)
# wip       : work in progress
# ----------- END INSTRUCTIONS ---------------------------------- >8 -|

